<TEXT>
here at a glance are facts and figures about mexico 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
geography mexico forms the southern part of north america 
connecting the central american isthmus with the bulk of the 
continent it shares a 2062mile border with the united states 
defined by the 1848 treaty of hidalgo in which mexico gave up half 
its territory for 15 million guatemala and belize border mexico 
to the southeast there are 31 states and the federal district the 
core area of the mexico city metropolitan area 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
population mexico has 80 million people 20 million of whom 
live in the mexico city metropolitan area about 55 percent of 
mexicans are of spanishindian heritage 29 percent are indian and 
10 percent caucasian more than 90 percent of mexicans are roman 
catholic spanish is the official language 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
government the government a federal republic is headed by 
president miguel de la madrid 53 a member of the institutional 
revolutionary party or pri he became president dec 1 1982 and 
his term ends on nov 30 the power of the mexican presidency 
overshadows mexicos judiciary and legislature all 44 members of 
the senate belong to the pri an electoral reform law provides for 
the number of seats reserved for opposition parties to expand from 
100 to 150 in the chamber of deputies which is increasing this 
year to 500 members 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
economy mexico has a mixed economy with the government holding 
several key industries it is heavily dependent on oil the primary 
source of revenues needed to pay its 104 billion foreign debt the 
developing worlds secondhighest oil exports earned 79 billion 
in 1987 inflation reached a record 1592 percent last year and 
the government froze wages prices and the pesodollar exchange 
rate to bring it under control inflation was 324 percent between 
january and april 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

