<TEXT>
a nuclear weapons test rocked the nevada 
desert today registering 56 on the richter scale and causing a 
swaying motion in highrise buildings here 100 miles from ground 
zero 
john minsch a spokesman for the national earthquake information 
center in golden colo said the reading indicated the test was 
one of the larger ones conducted at the desert site 
the device was detonated 40 miles from mercury a tiny town on 
the nevada test site where soviet nuclear scientists are based 
while preparing for a joint ussoviet test next month 
a controller in the tower at mccarran international airport in 
las vegas said the tower rocked slightly seconds after the blast 
at 805 am 
a telephone switchboard operator at fitzgeralds hotel in 
downtown las vegas said a guest on the 29th floor called to ask why 
she felt ground motion 
and a receptionist at the lionel sawyer law firm atop a 
highrise office building downtown said she felt a dizzy 
swirling feeling at the time of the blast she said a hanging 
plant in the office began swaying 
all three declined to give their names 
motion was recorded on energy department seismographs atop 
several hotelcasinos on the las vegas strip and downtown motion 
was also recorded at scottys castle in death valley calif west 
of the test site 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographsan earthquake or explosion of 35 on the richter scale 
can cause slight damage in the local area 4 moderate damage 5 
considerable damage 6 severe damage 
the test was delayed five minutes while controllers checked out 
a malfunctioning signal 
energy department spokesman chris west said the test appeared to 
be normal with no indications of any problems west who was in a 
control center 25 miles from ground zero said monitors at the site 
indicated no radiation had escaped the ground 
he said slight ground motion was felt in the control center 
todays test was the eighth conducted this year and the sixth 
conducted with soviet scientists on site 
the soviet scientists arrived earlier this year to begin 
preparing for next months joint verification experiment the 
soviet scientists will monitor a us test in midaugust and us 
scientists will monitor a soviet test a month later 
the experiments are designed to determine the ability of each 
country to monitor the size of the others tests such monitoring 
capabilities are critical in test limitation treaties 
the doe had issued a warning to managers of highrise buildings 
in las vegas not to have workers in precarious positions at the 
time of todays detonation such warnings are issued only when the 
test is near 150 kilotons the upper limits allowable under 
ussoviet treaties 
the nuclear device was buried 2000 feet beneath the surface of 
pahute mesa about 100 miles northwest of las vegas 
the most recent previous test was june 22 when two nuclear 
devices were detonated simultaneously in a rare experiment 
</TEXT>
