officials said a consensus was forming around a few key 
proposals that could well be included in relief legislation they 
said the measure most likely would allow farmers to keep all of the 
socalled deficiency payments that they have received in advance 
deficiency payments are incomesupport subsidies they represent 
the difference between the market price of the crop and a target 
price set by congress and adjusted by the secretary of agriculture 
as the drought has intensified crop prices have been rising in 
anticipation of scarcity later thus the gap between market prices 
and target prices has shrunk leaving farmers with smaller payments 
at the same time that their crops have been wiped out forty 
percent of the deficiency payments however already were parceled 
out in advance to producers 
i think it would be very difficult to collect advance 
deficiency payments from farmers who have no income lyng told 
reporters 
the officials also said that producers of nonprogram crops 
should also receive relief under the legislation soybeans 
constitute the largest of these crops whose producers do not 
receive deficiency payments various other fruits and vegetables 
also are nonprogram crops 
the officials were less clear on exactly how much the measure 
would cost 
de la garza and others emphasized that the cost of the drought 
bill would not be able to push the cost of farm subsidies over 
their budgeted 17 billion limit lawmakers are expecting to save a 
considerable sum as a result of the smaller size of deficiency 
payments to many farmers 
this amount in turn could be recycled and paid out in the form 
of drought relief but that still would not take in aid to growers 
of nonprogram crops 
that was discussed in there said rep charles stenholm 
dtexas he said it was unsure where the money would come from 
governors made clear however that some form of relief was 
needed 
farmers in missouri would face a a real economic disaster from 
which they would not recover if we failed to get relief said 
ashcroft we will get relief 
