apollo computer another otc issue tumbled 4 to 10 thea braid factory 
and as a mailman before 
joining the police force his stellar record got him into law 
school without benefit of a high school diploma 
after law school biaggi worked for republican gov nelson 
rockefeller but was bounced from a post as assistant secretary of 
state in 1965 after refusing an order to take unpaid leave instead 
of vacation to work on the mayoral campaign of abraham beame 
beame lost that race to john lindsay 
in 1968 biaggi was elected to congress to fill the seat of 
republican paul fino who had been appointed a judge he has been 
reelected every two years with overwhelming majorities he became 
known as a lawandorder democrat an advocate of handgun control 
and an opponent of british rule in northern ireland 
but one office always eluded him he desperately wanted to be 
elected mayor of new york city 
why did he want to be mayor 
why do people climb the himalayas he replied 
in 1972 he made a run for the job and looked to be a shooin 
for the democratic nomination which in new york city is tantamount 
to election but biaggis candidacy was destroyed by a series of 
investigations and allegations which culminated in his being 
proven a liar 
at the time biaggi was questioned by a grand jury looking into 
allegations of payoffs to congressmen who sponsored certain 
immigration legislation when reports surfaced that biaggi had 
taken the fifth amendment before the panel he vehemently denied it 
he sued to have some but not all of the record made public 
but the tactic backfired when the judge released all the minutes 
proving biaggi had in fact asserted his right to not to incriminate 
himself 
beame was elected mayor and biaggi went back to congress 
in 1986 new accusations were leveled at biaggi and these began 
to stick 
first he was indicted for illegally accepting paid vacations in 
exchange for using his influence to steer federal contracts to 
coastal dry dock and repair a brooklyn shipyard he was convicted 
of taking a gratuity illegal interstate travel and obstruction 
but he wept when he was sentenced to 2 years in prison and fined 
500000 biaggi is appealing the decision 
a second indictment accused him of using the wedtech corp a 
bronxbased machine company as a racketeering enterprise the case 
is now on trial in new york and biaggi is charged with accepting 
millions of dollars worth of company stock issued in his sons 
name in exchange for helping the company get military contracts 
his son and four others are on trial with biaggi 
the house of representatives forced biaggi to relinquish his 
subcommittee chairmanships after the first indictment last year and 
to refrain from voting after his conviction in september but those 
moves were slaps on the wrist compared to what was to come 
in february the house committee on standards of official 
conduct recommended that biaggi be expelled for criminal conduct 
going to the heart of his representational responsibilities 
in an unusual maneuver however congressional leaders decided to 
delay action while biaggi defended himself in the wedtech trial in 
